# What NOT to upload to the host.
#
# NOTE: no environment variables are needed on Vercel. The palette makes no LLM calls at
# runtime -- the model is vendored and loaded locally (command-palette.js sets
# allowRemoteModels = false). LLM_API_KEY is read only by generate_eval.js /
# generate_descriptions.js, on a developer's machine. A key in the host's env would add
# exposure and buy nothing.
#
# Do NOT add build_snapshots.py, generate_embeddings.js, ranking.js or package*.json here:
# Vercel runs `npm run build`, which needs all four (generate_embeddings.js imports
# ranking.js). Excluding them breaks the deploy.

# Secrets. Also gitignored; belt and braces for CLI deploys, which do not read .gitignore.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

node_modules/

# Dev-only: the eval harness and its data. Not part of the build, not needed to serve the
# site, and no reason to publish at https://<site>/generate_eval.js
eval/
generate_eval.js
generate_descriptions.js

# Local launcher; pointless on a served origin.
Start Demo.bat
